Combined upstream fixes for grid memory corruption in tmux 3.6a.

Backports the following commits from tmux master:

- 035a2f35: Clear trimmed lines after moving (issue 4790)
- f2184639: grid_peek_cell can return NULL (issue 4848)
- fedd4440: Reuse extended entry when clearing RGB cell
- 03104041: Reuse extended slot when clearing non-RGB cells
- 2c7f73f9: Do not use recallocarray (size mismatch after reflow)
- f7dad4f3: Check lastgc is not NULL (issue 4935)
- 4b0ff07b: grid_clear_cell moved flag (extended data reuse after move)

Defensive hardening (not from upstream):

- grid_adjust_lines: zero-initialize newly allocated linedata entries
  after xreallocarray, preventing garbage pointers if a caller omits
  initialization
- grid_compact_line: bounds-check extended cell offsets before access,
  stripping GRID_FLAG_EXTENDED from cells with corrupt offsets to prevent
  out-of-bounds reads into heap metadata

